Polling approach

Exception Handling in Callable:
Future<Integer> future = executor.submit(() -> {
    throw new RuntimeException("Error");
});
try {
    future.get();
} catch (ExecutionException e) {
    System.out.println("Exception: " + e.getCause());
}
Exception wrapped in: ExecutionException

ExecutorService:
  ExecutorService is a high-level API to manage threads using a thread pool.
  Instead of new Thread(...).start(); use ExecutorService executor = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(3);
  Manual thread creation:
          Expensive ❌
          Hard to manage ❌
          No reuse ❌
  ExecutorService solves:
          Thread reuse
          Task scheduling
          Lifecycle management
Most implementations use: ThreadPoolExecutor
Components: Worker threads,Task queue and Rejection policy

execute():  Takes Runnable only, Returns void, no results and throws exception directly
executor.execute(() -> {
    System.out.println("Task executed");
});
submit(): takes Callable and Runnable. Returns Future and tracks results and Exceptions wrapped in ExecutionException
Future<Integer> future = executor.submit(() -> {
    return 10;
});
